.TH "dma_port_flash_write" 9 "dma_port_flash_write" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dma_port_flash_write \- Write to non-active flash region
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" dma_port_flash_write
.BI "(struct tb_dma_port *dma "  ","
.BI "unsigned int address "  ","
.BI "const void *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dma" 12
DMA control port
.IP "address" 12
Address relative to the start of non-active region
.IP "buf" 12
Data to write
.IP "size" 12
Size of the buffer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Writes block of data to the non-active flash region of the switch. If
the address is given as DMA_PORT_CSS_ADDRESS the block is written
using CSS command.
